		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Mar 22nd 8:04 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=111153649186972351&num=12&post=1&replyto=1111539830185036240"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1111539830185036240></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9795 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.02]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b id="fs8">Caiapfas wrote:</b><hr size="1" />I have a few questions..<br><br>1. what lvl are the ice giants in everfrost? (can my lvl 41 pally solo them?)<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>As stated above. Probably not. They're going to hit pretty hard for your level. There are much better places to hunt then ICs in EF though. I'd ignore them IMO.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />2. where do i get my merchant bag from in bazaar?<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>See answer above. Sometimes you need to just explore zones and find things.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />3. if i buy a bridial from bazaar, how do i know how my horse will look?<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>I'll add something here. Each type of bridle comes in 4 different colors, black, white, brown, and tan. The different types of bridles affect only the speed of the horse. The colors reflect the color of the horse. If you want an idea of what the horse will look like, wander around the stable area and look at the horses there. Did you not notice there were horses in the stalls right in that same room? That's what they look like...<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />4. how do i get a backpack in bazzar and are they free?<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Same answer. Look around. I know you are new to EQ, but this is something you realy do have to just learn to do. When in a city check out the vendors. That's how you learn which vendors sell what. There's a certain amount of logic though. A vendor in a leathershop is likely to sell leather armor and bags. A vendor in a jewelry shop is likely to sell gems and jewelcrafting gear. A vendor in a fishing shop is likely to sell fishing poles, bait, and other fishing gear. A vendor in an archery shop is likely to sell archery supplies as well as cheap bows and arrows.<br><br>Look around. They didn't go through the trouble of putting signs on the outside of buildings for nothing.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />noob, question..does my HP and otehr stats go up when i lvl?<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>How'd you get to level 41 without knowing this? ;)<br><br>I'll go into a bit of game theory here. Most games have two types of &quot;stats&quot;.<br><br>Primary stats are those that are rolled/selected when you start your character. They are very basic indications of the capabilities of your character without any regards to experience gained. So things like strength and wisdom and intelligence are primary stats. As a general rule, they don't change as you gain levels (there are some games with exceptions, but EQ is not one of them.<br><br>Secondary or &quot;figured&quot; stats are stats that are based on calculations of the primary stats and other things (like skills or levels of the character). Secondary stats in EQ are things like HPs, endurance, and mana.<br><br>Both HPs and mana increase as you level (I assume endurance does as well). In the case of HPs, the amount you gain per level is based on your class. Warriors gain the most, then the knights (paladins and shadowknights), and so on down to the int casters who gain the least per level. Additionally, there are multiples of HPs gained based on your stamina stat (this is where the figured part comes in). So extra stamina points added to a warrior will give him more extra HPs then that same stamina points added to a wizard. Interestingly enough, as far as I know, all characters that can use mana gain it at the same rate regardless of class. Back in the day, hybrids used to get less mana per level, and less mana gained from increased int/wis, but at some point the game designers changed that. I'm not totally sure how endurance is calculated to be honest...<br><br><br>Primary stats can (and will!) increase though. They don't go up automatically as you gain levels, but you will obtain gear that increases them while you wear the gear, and buff spells can increase them temporarily as well. Additionally, at the higher level (51+) there are Alternate Advancement points you can gain (you allocate experience to go to AA instead of leveling to get them). Those points can be spent on increasing your natural primary stat levels (but generally it's a bad idea to waste the points this way since gear is pretty sufficient for maxing out stats, and the AA points are better spent elsewhere).<br><br>Probably more then you wanted to know...</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
